# ROLE: Senior Frontend Architect
# TASK: Build a High-End, Data-Driven Portfolio Website (Zero-Framework)

## 1. TECHNICAL CONSTRAINTS (MANDATORY)
- Language: Pure Vanilla JS (ESModules), HTML5, CSS3.
- NO Frameworks (React, Vue...), NO NPM/Node.js, NO Build Tools, NO Libraries.
- Deployment: Optimized for GitHub Pages.
- Architecture: Component-Based Architecture (Object-Oriented Programming).

## 2. PROJECT STRUCTURE
You must implement the following directory structure:
/
├── index.html                  # Minimal entry HTML
├── data/
│   ├── profile.json            # Main array: [{id, title, desc, image, dataPath}]
│   └── modules/                # Specialized detail JSONs (e.g., minecraft.json)
├── src/
│   ├── app.js                  # App Orchestrator: Fetches profile.json & inits Components
│   ├── core/
│   │   └── Component.js        # Base Class: Handles dynamic CSS loading & rendering logic
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── Card/
│   │   │   ├── Card.js         # Card Logic: Auto-render from data, handles click events
│   │   │   └── Card.css        # Glassmorphism, Image Hover, Shimmer effects
│   │   └── Panel/
│   │       ├── Panel.js        # Panel Logic: Fetch detailed JSON, open/close states
│   │       └── Panel.css       # Backdrop-blur, Clip-path animations, Responsive layout
│   └── styles/
│       ├── variables.css       # Design System: Colors, Gradients, Cubic-bezier, Blur-values
│       └── global.css          # Reset, Typography (Inter/System-ui), Main Grid layout

## 3. CORE FEATURES & LOGIC
- DATA-DRIVEN: 'app.js' must loop through 'profile.json' and instantiate a new 'Card' object for each entry. UI must update automatically when JSON changes.
- DYNAMIC SCOPED CSS: Each component must call 'loadStyle()' from the Base Class to inject its CSS only when needed.
- PANEL VIEWER: When a Card is clicked, 'Panel.js' must fetch data from the provided 'dataPath' and render a detailed view.
- PERFORMANCE & UX:
    * Skeleton Loading: Show shimmer effect while fetching data.
    * Fade-in Scale: Images must have a smooth fade + scale animation on load.
    * High-End Transitions: Use 'cubic-bezier(0.19, 1, 0.22, 1)' for all movements.
    * Glassmorphism: Heavy use of backdrop-filter, subtle borders, and low-opacity backgrounds.

## 4. OUTPUT REQUIREMENT
- Provide COMPLETE source code for every single file mentioned in the structure.
- Ensure all ESModule imports include the '.js' extension for browser compatibility.
- Code must be clean, professional, and production-ready.
- NO snippets, NO abbreviations. Write the full implementation.

